[
  {
    "text": "Acids and bases are everywhere.",
    "start": 6.606,
    "duration": 2.033
  },
  {
    "text": "They're used to make foods,",
    "start": 8.639,
    "duration": 1.576
  },
  {
    "text": "soaps and detergents,",
    "start": 10.215,
    "duration": 1.325
  },
  {
    "text": "fertilizers,",
    "start": 11.54,
    "duration": 0.776
  },
  {
    "text": "explosives,",
    "start": 12.316,
    "duration": 1.169
  },
  {
    "text": "dyes,",
    "start": 13.485,
    "duration": 0.715
  },
  {
    "text": "plastics,",
    "start": 14.2,
    "duration": 0.45
  },
  {
    "text": "pesticides,",
    "start": 14.65,
    "duration": 0.662
  },
  {
    "text": "even paper.",
    "start": 15.312,
    "duration": 1.233
  },
  {
    "text": "Our stomachs are very acidic.",
    "start": 16.545,
    "duration": 1.667
  },
  {
    "text": "Our blood is slightly basic.",
    "start": 18.212,
    "duration": 1.826
  },
  {
    "text": "Our proteins are made up of amino acids,",
    "start": 20.038,
    "duration": 2.869
  },
  {
    "text": "and the letters in our genetic code,",
    "start": 22.907,
    "duration": 1.716
  },
  {
    "text": "those As, Ts, Cs, and Gs,",
    "start": 24.623,
    "duration": 2.205
  },
  {
    "text": "are all bases.",
    "start": 26.828,
    "duration": 1.821
  },
  {
    "text": "You were probably taught",
    "start": 28.649,
    "duration": 0.859
  },
  {
    "text": "how acids and bases behave",
    "start": 29.508,
    "duration": 1.356
  },
  {
    "text": "on the molecular level.",
    "start": 30.864,
    "duration": 1.586
  },
  {
    "text": "You were probably never taught",
    "start": 32.45,
    "duration": 1.679
  },
  {
    "text": "that a long time ago,",
    "start": 34.129,
    "duration": 1.118
  },
  {
    "text": "like ancient Greek ago,",
    "start": 35.247,
    "duration": 2.058
  },
  {
    "text": "before anyone knew about atoms or molecules,",
    "start": 37.305,
    "duration": 2.368
  },
  {
    "text": "acids and bases were defined",
    "start": 39.673,
    "duration": 1.539
  },
  {
    "text": "by how they behaved.",
    "start": 41.212,
    "duration": 1.796
  },
  {
    "text": "Acids tasted sour and corroded metal.",
    "start": 43.008,
    "duration": 3.452
  },
  {
    "text": "Bases felt slippery",
    "start": 46.46,
    "duration": 1.66
  },
  {
    "text": "and could somehow counteract acids.",
    "start": 48.12,
    "duration": 2.814
  },
  {
    "text": "When molecules dissolved in water interact,",
    "start": 52.395,
    "duration": 2.204
  },
  {
    "text": "they are exchanging two main currencies",
    "start": 54.599,
    "duration": 1.941
  },
  {
    "text": "with their surroundings:",
    "start": 56.54,
    "duration": 1.658
  },
  {
    "text": "protons, also known as hydrogen ions,",
    "start": 58.198,
    "duration": 2.837
  },
  {
    "text": "and electrons.",
    "start": 61.035,
    "duration": 1.413
  },
  {
    "text": "Depending on how a molecule is composed or shaped,",
    "start": 62.448,
    "duration": 2.891
  },
  {
    "text": "it may be willing to donate or accept",
    "start": 65.339,
    "duration": 2.198
  },
  {
    "text": "either protons or electrons",
    "start": 67.537,
    "duration": 1.581
  },
  {
    "text": "with some other community member.",
    "start": 69.118,
    "duration": 2.213
  },
  {
    "text": "And some molecules are far more aggressive than others",
    "start": 71.331,
    "duration": 3.096
  },
  {
    "text": "when it comes to donating or accepting either currency.",
    "start": 74.427,
    "duration": 3.446
  },
  {
    "text": "Remember that protons are positively charged",
    "start": 77.873,
    "duration": 2.082
  },
  {
    "text": "and electrons are negatively charged.",
    "start": 79.955,
    "duration": 2.325
  },
  {
    "text": "So, if a molecule is willing to give up a proton,",
    "start": 82.28,
    "duration": 2.7
  },
  {
    "text": "that's not too different",
    "start": 84.98,
    "duration": 1.25
  },
  {
    "text": "from it being willing to accept an electron --",
    "start": 86.23,
    "duration": 2.515
  },
  {
    "text": "either way it's becoming more negatively charged.",
    "start": 88.745,
    "duration": 3.235
  },
  {
    "text": "Other molecules are willing to accept a proton",
    "start": 91.98,
    "duration": 2.509
  },
  {
    "text": "or give up an electron.",
    "start": 94.489,
    "duration": 1.838
  },
  {
    "text": "These are becoming more positively charged.",
    "start": 96.327,
    "duration": 2.322
  },
  {
    "text": "Some substances are so aggressive",
    "start": 98.649,
    "duration": 2.391
  },
  {
    "text": "about donating their protons",
    "start": 101.04,
    "duration": 1.532
  },
  {
    "text": "that when they get a chance,",
    "start": 102.572,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "all of the molecules in a sample",
    "start": 103.782,
    "duration": 1.838
  },
  {
    "text": "will dump a proton,",
    "start": 105.62,
    "duration": 1.374
  },
  {
    "text": "sometimes more than one,",
    "start": 106.994,
    "duration": 1.294
  },
  {
    "text": "to the surrounding water molecules.",
    "start": 108.288,
    "duration": 1.997
  },
  {
    "text": "We call these strong acids.",
    "start": 110.285,
    "duration": 2.835
  },
  {
    "text": "Meanwhile, some compounds are so ready",
    "start": 113.12,
    "duration": 1.717
  },
  {
    "text": "to accept a proton",
    "start": 114.837,
    "duration": 1.28
  },
  {
    "text": "that they won't wait around,",
    "start": 116.117,
    "duration": 1.252
  },
  {
    "text": "they'll just rip one off water,",
    "start": 117.369,
    "duration": 1.64
  },
  {
    "text": "which usually has two protons",
    "start": 119.009,
    "duration": 1.526
  },
  {
    "text": "but is generous enough to hang out with just one.",
    "start": 120.535,
    "duration": 2.608
  },
  {
    "text": "We call these strong bases.",
    "start": 123.143,
    "duration": 2.37
  },
  {
    "text": "Other acids and bases are not so strong.",
    "start": 125.513,
    "duration": 2.79
  },
  {
    "text": "They may donate just a few of their protons to water",
    "start": 128.303,
    "duration": 3.01
  },
  {
    "text": "or accept just a few protons from water,",
    "start": 131.313,
    "duration": 2.329
  },
  {
    "text": "but most of their molecules stay exactly the same.",
    "start": 133.642,
    "duration": 3.066
  },
  {
    "text": "If left alone in water,",
    "start": 136.708,
    "duration": 1.704
  },
  {
    "text": "they'll reach some equilibrium point",
    "start": 138.412,
    "duration": 1.831
  },
  {
    "text": "where maybe only one out of a hundred",
    "start": 140.243,
    "duration": 1.83
  },
  {
    "text": "or one out of ten thousand of their molecules",
    "start": 142.073,
    "duration": 1.833
  },
  {
    "text": "has exchanged currency with water.",
    "start": 143.906,
    "duration": 2.549
  },
  {
    "text": "As you might guess,",
    "start": 146.455,
    "duration": 1.122
  },
  {
    "text": "we label these acids and bases weak,",
    "start": 147.577,
    "duration": 2.582
  },
  {
    "text": "but in the common sense of the word,",
    "start": 150.159,
    "duration": 1.292
  },
  {
    "text": "they're not weak.",
    "start": 151.451,
    "duration": 1.296
  },
  {
    "text": "The vinegar in your salad dressing",
    "start": 152.747,
    "duration": 1.625
  },
  {
    "text": "that you can smell from across the room,",
    "start": 154.372,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "that is a weak acid.",
    "start": 156.124,
    "duration": 2.083
  },
  {
    "text": "The ammonia you spray on glass",
    "start": 158.207,
    "duration": 1.22
  },
  {
    "text": "for a streak-free shine,",
    "start": 159.427,
    "duration": 1.126
  },
  {
    "text": "that is a weak base.",
    "start": 160.553,
    "duration": 1.867
  },
  {
    "text": "So, it doesn't take much to be an active player",
    "start": 162.42,
    "duration": 2.638
  },
  {
    "text": "in the chemical economy.",
    "start": 165.058,
    "duration": 1.88
  },
  {
    "text": "Most acid-base chemistry takes place in water,",
    "start": 167.676,
    "duration": 2.673
  },
  {
    "text": "which can act as either an acid or a base,",
    "start": 170.349,
    "duration": 2.719
  },
  {
    "text": "accepting deposits and enabling withdrawals",
    "start": 173.068,
    "duration": 1.928
  },
  {
    "text": "like a 24-hour molecular ATM.",
    "start": 174.996,
    "duration": 2.827
  },
  {
    "text": "And when a proton-deposit customer,",
    "start": 177.823,
    "duration": 2.261
  },
  {
    "text": "that's an acid,",
    "start": 180.084,
    "duration": 1.075
  },
  {
    "text": "and a proton-withdrawal customer,",
    "start": 181.159,
    "duration": 2.371
  },
  {
    "text": "the base,",
    "start": 183.53,
    "duration": 0.81
  },
  {
    "text": "shop at the same time,",
    "start": 184.34,
    "duration": 1.381
  },
  {
    "text": "their net effect on water's account",
    "start": 185.721,
    "duration": 1.782
  },
  {
    "text": "may cancel out,",
    "start": 187.503,
    "duration": 1.584
  },
  {
    "text": "and we call this neutralization.",
    "start": 189.087,
    "duration": 2.65
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, certain molecules can behave",
    "start": 191.737,
    "duration": 1.945
  },
  {
    "text": "as acids or bases without water,",
    "start": 193.682,
    "duration": 2.207
  },
  {
    "text": "but that's another story.",
    "start": 195.889,
    "duration": 1.58
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's end by saluting water",
    "start": 197.469,
    "duration": 1.67
  },
  {
    "text": "as the resilient and fair banker",
    "start": 199.139,
    "duration": 1.751
  },
  {
    "text": "for acids and bases.",
    "start": 200.89,
    "duration": 1.828
  },
  {
    "text": "It's always open for business,",
    "start": 202.718,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "doesn't charge interest,",
    "start": 204.02,
    "duration": 1.202
  },
  {
    "text": "and will never foreclose on your molecules,",
    "start": 205.222,
    "duration": 2.3
  },
  {
    "text": "which is more than I can say for [bleep].",
    "start": 207.522,
    "duration": 2.941
  },
  {
    "text": "Waah-waah.",
    "start": 210.816,
    "duration": 1.125
  }
]